ne; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">　</span>博士后</span><br></p></div>                 \n    <div class=\"tli-content tli-content-\"><p style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 2em;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\">● 合作讲授《辐射成像原理》研究生课程<br>● 合作讲授《核数据获取与处理及课程设计》本科生课程</span><br></p></div>                 \n    <div class=\"tli-content tli-content-\"><p style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 2em;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\">● X射线成像， 特别是相衬、散射成像及其在生物医学和材料科学中的应用<br>● X射线成像方法和系统的前沿研究与技术创新</span><br></p></div>                 \n    <div class=\"tli-content tli-content-\"><p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; text-align: justify; line-height: 2em; text-indent: 2em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50); font-family: 微软雅黑,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">自1895年伦琴发现X射线以来， 医学和工业中应用的X射线成像的基本原理——物质对于X光的吸收效应——没有发生任何变化。随着先进X射线光源、光学元件、探测器和成像方法的发展，如今的X射线成像可以同时获取吸收、相衬、散射等多种物理信息，极大地提高了所获取信息的维度。X射线成像进入了“文艺复兴“的时代！ 探索新的成像方法及其在生物医学和材料科学中的应用充满了令人激动的挑战和机遇，打造国际一流的成像平台服务于其他学科在影像学方面的需要则是我研究工作的源动力。 </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; line-height: 1.5em; text-indent: 2em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50); font-family: 微软雅黑,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; line-height: 1.5em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50); font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei; font-size: 14px;\">过往研究工作及代表性成果：</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; line-height: 1.5em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50); font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei; font-size: 14px;\">● 相衬成像在乳腺成像中的应用及样机研发</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; line-height: 1.5em;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50); font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei; font-size: 14px;\">● 多衬度成像方法创新及在材料科学中的应</span><span style=\"color: rgb(50, 50, 50); font-family: 微软雅黑,sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">用</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>                 \n    <div class=\"tli-content tli-content-\"><p style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 2em; text-indent: 0em;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\">5篇代表性论文：<br><span style=\"text-align: left; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">　　</span>● Diffractive small angle X-ray scattering imaging for anisotropic structures. Kagias，M.，Wang，Z.，Birkbak，E. M.，Lauridsen，E.，Abis，M.，Lovric，G.，Jefimovs，K.，Stampanoni，M.，Nature Communications 10，5130 (2019)<br><span style=\"text-align: left; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">　　</span>●&nbsp;2D-Omnidirectional Hard-X-Ray Scattering Sensitivity in a Single Shot，Kagias，M.，Wang，Z.，Villanueva-Perez，P.，Jefimovs，K.，Stampanoni，M.，Phys. Rev. Lett. 116，093902 (2016)&nbsp;<br> <span style=\"text-align: left; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">　　</span>● No-invasive classification of microcalcifications with phase-contrast X-ray mammography，Wang，Z.，Hauser，N.，Singer，G.，Trippel，M.，Kubik-Huch，R. A.，Schneider，C. W.，Stampanoni，M.，Nature Communications 5，3797 (2014)&nbsp;<br> <span style=\"text-align: left; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"></span><span style=\"text-align: left; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\"><span style=\"text-align: left; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; -ms-word-break: normal !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; text-decoration-line: none;\">　　</span><span style=\"text-align: justify; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: 微软雅黑, &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">● </span></span>The first analysis and clinical evaluation of native breast tissue using differential phase-contrast mammography. Stampanoni，M.，Wang，Z.，Thüring，T.，David，C.，Roessl，E.，Trippel，M.，Kubik-Huch，R. A.，Singer，G.，Hohl，M. K.，Hauser，N.，Investigative radiology，46(12): 801-806 (2011)<br><span style=\"text-align: left; color: rgb(50, 50, 50); text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; font-family: &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; word-spacing: 0px; float: none; display: inline !important; orphans: 2; widows: 2; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;\">　　</span>●&nbsp;Quantitative grating-based x-ray dark-field computed tomography. Wang，Z.，Kang，K.，Huang，Z.，Chen，Z.，Applied Physics Letters，95(9):094105 (2009)</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 2em;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\"><br>期刊文章列表： </span><a href=\"https://goo.gl/frcCAH\" target=\"_blank\" textvalue=\"https://goo.gl/frcCAH\" style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei; text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\">https://goo.gl/frcCAH</span></a><br><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\">专利列表： </span><a href=\"https://goo.gl/aK1qYc\" target=\"_blank\" textvalue=\"https://goo.gl/aK1qYc\" style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei; text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\">https://goo.gl/aK1qYc</span></a><br></p></div>                 \n    <div class=\"tli-content tli-content-\"><p style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 2em;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑,Microsoft YaHei;\"><span style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑, &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;; text-align: justify;\